Requirements of the MA thesis and MA project; overview of internship opportunities; choosing and formulating the topic of the MA thesis or MA project, explaining its relevance; selecting theoretical and other relevant secondary literature; setting a time frame; mapping knowledge and skills needed to complete the given task; devising and presenting a proposal for an MA thesis or MA project.Objectives/eesmärkid:  This course aims to increase students' skills in identifying and formulating research problems and topics, in planning research and projects of other kinds, and in developing their capability to reflect on their professional abilities and needs.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon successful completion of this course, students should:
*	have devised a written proposal for an MA thesis or MA project, laying out the topic, aims, theoretical and methodological starting points and time frame of the project/thesis;
*	be capable of explaining the relevance of the chosen topic and how the proposed thesis/project is linked to and different from other studies/projects on related topics;
*	be capable of analysing potential risks and problems, and opportunities to prevent them, and of finding ethical solutions;
*	be capable of charting their skills, knowledge and needs for personal professional development.
